All Python code you write or edit MUST strictly adhere to the PEP 8 style guide.

- Use strict Python type hints (from the `typing` module) for all function signatures and variables.
- Add clear, concise comments to explain the "why" behind complex or non-obvious blocks of code, not just the "what".